OL,3,CRoyal Mail set to cut deliveries as
OL,4,Cpart of cost-saving proposals
OL,6,FFigures from Ofcom show the number of
OL,7,Fletters delivered each year has
OL,8,Fplummeted from 20 billion letters two
OL,9,Fdecades ago, to 6.6 billion now.
OL,11,FEmma Gilthorpe, Chief Executive of
OL,12,FRoyal Mail, said: "Reform is crucial
OL,13,Fto support a modern, sustainable, and
OL,14,Freliable postal service for our
OL,15,Fcustomers, our company and our people."
OL,17,F"But we're safeguarding what matters
OL,18,Fmost to people ` first class mail six
OL,19,Fdays a week at the same price
OL,20,Fthroughout the UK, and a price cap on
OL,21,Fsecond class stamps."
